race.description: Thoroughbred Breeders Wa Platinum Classic Hcp
race.comment: GALWAY SHAWL (6) was impressive first-up at Bunbury when settling last and rounding up her rivals with ease. She'll be fitter for that effort and the rise in trip won't be an issue. This is tougher, but she's a very progressive type and she can continue her winning ways. SUPERNATURAL (3) disappointed last time out when settling last and never getting into the race. That form has already been franked however and now Pike hops on board, replacing the apprentice. Onto the bigger track should suit and she can bounce back to form. GOLDEN VALE (1) is a classy mare first-up here and will be fitter for two trials coming in. He usually goes well fresh and the claim of Cooper comes in handy. Maps well and can make an impression. PINGERS (10) is up in grade here but is winning well this time in work. Include with no weight on her back. RISSOLES (4) is better than we saw last time in work and she can bounce back to form here with Parnham on board.
